<br>
Perhaps they knew it was due, and they are just accepting it. Am I happy it happened? Well, yes and no.<br>
<br>
Yes, because the Shadowzerks were a little stronger than intended. They were not meant to do the damage they are, and LA gave them a way to outmelee most classes. A majority of the reason the assassin class' melee was reduced was due to the fact that the Shadzerks were taking down tanks and what not. Even after that, Shadzerks were still taking down the light tanks with little to no problem.<br>
<br>
No, because the Zerks are being heavily affected by this, and it is one of thier defining features. I feel sorry for our brothers-in-arms.<br>
<br>
Now, what does this mean for the skald? Very little. LA is not one of our skills. It is not something we are known for. Why are we arguing about it when we have nothing to do with it?<br>
<br>
Now, does the Block/Parry thing hurt us abit? Well, in a matter of speaking, yes, it does. But it was a bug, and a bug in bad need of fixing. Bravo to Mythic for this one.<br>
<br>
And as for people cancelling, go ahead. If you feel the game is going to be lessened for you because this patch is going in, so be it. Me? Im just going to keep going on, and find other ways to take down those I have to. <br>
<br>
After all, whats victory without struggle?<br>
