<br>
Right now, the LA does not affect skalds directly.  But the loss of end regen does.  When it goes live and the shamans cant buff everyone, only the tanks and casters will get shaman buffs.  Skalds, as support classses, will not get priority for anything.  So, we will be losing end buffs, and possibly the dual buffs.  That, my firends, will kill the skald.  We will be relegated to taxi more and more in the battlefield.  And I already dont like how my sklad plays in RvR.  Only way to survive is 1v1 or zerging.  And usually I die anyhow. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kortzdymundskyn>Kortz Dymundskyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/28/03 1:20:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=588.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Patch killing skalds</span><hr size=1> Thank you Kilgour. <br>
<br>
That I can understand, and see how we Skalds are going to be hurt by the patch overall. I agree that since we have lower priority over some of the more warrior types (Zerks, Wars, Thanes), we wont be as effective in RVR (this almost sounds like an oxymoron) due to the fact we will be out of End much faster, and thus our sprint to escape and our ability to style will be just annoyances on the battlefield, not true meaningful ways of damage.<br>
<br>
However, we are the speed class in Midgard. As much as we hate to think of ourselves with only one purpose, and that being to ferry people about, it is sad to say that it is basically what we are. Until Mythic defines what we are supposed to be (fighting caster, casting fighter, support fighter, light tank), we are stuck with this role.<br>
<br>
I still think we should get the End Regen chant, IMO. Take it away from the Shaman, and give us a reason to actually support the classes of our realm. Something else to let us do our jobs of being a support class, if that is in fact what we are. Not only would we have a reason to be asked for, but the Shaman could concentrate more on the other buffs without having to worry about how many they have cast or conc left. This would also solve the whole range thing, as it would be a group chant, effective out to the range 1500 or what not. Just a thought....<br>
<br>
Oh yea, and can we have it fixed so that we stop showing up as healers in the Looking For (class type)? You know how annoying it is to get sent a tell to join a group, get where the group is, and then find out they thought you were a Healer, and not a Skald? <p>Bays Endruhms<br>
